From forthcoming CL http://codereview.chromium.org/3143040

The man page for sem_post says that if you attempt to call sem_post on a semaphore whose value is SEM_VALUE_MAX, sem_post will set errno to EOVERFLOW and return -1.  Currently, it appears to happily perform the post (at least on linux) since the underlying system calls have a higher value of SEM_VALUE_MAX.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-08-25T00:37:21.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-08-24T21:54:41.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Available</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
